 <unk> began as a trading post in the 1860s situated along the <unk> Military Road to take advantage of the first route across the <unk> Mountains to the plains of Eastern Washington . Its designation as county seat in 1866 and location of the hastily built Fort <unk> in 1877 ensured <unk> 's status as a regional commercial center ; a status further consolidated in 1883 with the arrival of the Northern Pacific Railway . The railroad expanded <unk> 's trade area to cover a 150 @-@ mile radius , and <unk> 's location as the railway 's division point and repair shops provided hundreds of jobs . When the railway began expanding again in 1898 , increased freight shipments came through the city , and with the arrival of the Milwaukee Road and regional office for the U.S. Forest Service as well as the opening of the <unk> Indian <unk> to settlement all within a couple years of each other beginning in 1908 , the economy began to rapidly expand . 
 Since opening in 1895 , the University of Montana has had a major impact on the development of <unk> 's economy . In addition to the economic advantage from <unk> the student body , it gave the city an educated workforce not available in most of the state . The university has a close relationship with the city as <unk> 's largest employer and with the millions of dollars the school brings into the city through visitors of school @-@ sponsored sporting and cultural events . The university also houses <unk> 's only business <unk> , the Montana Technology Enterprise Center ( <unk> ) , and several start @-@ up businesses . 
