 <unk> ( / <unk> , <unk> / ; Latin : Titus <unk> Caesar <unk> Augustus ; 24 October 51 – 18 September 96 ) was Roman emperor from 81 to 96 . <unk> was the third and last emperor of the <unk> dynasty . 
 <unk> 's youth and early career were largely spent in the shadow of his brother Titus , who gained military <unk> during the First Jewish – Roman War . This situation continued under the rule of his father <unk> , who became emperor in 69 following the civil war known as the Year of the Four <unk> . While Titus held a great many offices under the rule of his father , <unk> was left with honours but no responsibilities . <unk> died in 79 and was succeeded by Titus , whose own reign came to an unexpected end when he was struck by a fatal illness in 81 . The following day <unk> was declared Emperor by the <unk> Guard , commencing a reign that lasted fifteen years – longer than any man who had ruled since <unk> . 
 <unk> was born in Rome on 24 October 51 , the youngest son of Titus <unk> <unk> — commonly known as <unk> — and <unk> <unk> Major . He had an older sister , <unk> the Younger , and brother , also named Titus <unk> <unk> . 
 <unk> of civil war during the 1st century BC had contributed greatly to the demise of the old aristocracy of Rome , which a new Italian nobility gradually replaced in prominence during the early part of the 1st century . One such family , the <unk> , or <unk> <unk> , rose from relative obscurity to prominence in just four generations , acquiring wealth and status under the emperors of the Julio @-@ <unk> dynasty . <unk> 's great @-@ grandfather , Titus <unk> <unk> , had served as a <unk> under Pompey during Caesar 's civil war . His military career ended in disgrace when he fled the battlefield at the Battle of <unk> in 48 BC . 
 By all appearances , the <unk> enjoyed high imperial favour throughout the 40s and 60s . While Titus received a court education in the company of <unk> , <unk> pursued a successful political and military career . Following a prolonged period of retirement during the 50s , he returned to public office under <unk> , serving as <unk> of the Africa province in 63 , and accompanying the emperor during an official tour of Greece in 66 . 
